<paragraph id="C8639966FFFB2C0CF3D6FDE601419D63" blockId="1.[113,776,573,858]" pageId="1" pageNumber="236">
<emphasis id="FAA84574FFFB2C0CF3D6FDE601669C33" box="[136,547,573,594]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="236">Apothecia solitaria, discus acetabuliformis,</emphasis>
5-12 
<emphasis id="FAA84574FFFB2C0CF105FDE601F89C0E" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="236">mm diam, stipitatus, hymenio brunneo, stipes cylindraceus, colore simile disco,</emphasis>
5–20 × 0.8–1.5 
<emphasis id="FAA84574FFFB2C0CF3E1FDA302CF9CEC" box="[191,394,632,653]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="236">mm. Asci cylindracei,</emphasis>
† (120–)130–170 × 7–9 
<emphasis id="FAA84574FFFB2C0CF123FDA3024B9CA6" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="236">μm, octospori, poro jodo caerulescenti. Ascosporae uniseriatae, hyalinae, elipsoideae, inaequilaterales,</emphasis>
† 9.5–11.8 × 4.7–6.6 
<emphasis id="FAA84574FFFB2C0CF288FD69013E9CA6" box="[470,635,690,711]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="236">μm. Microconidia</emphasis>
2–4 
<emphasis id="FAA84574FFFB2C0CF1F6FD6900429C84" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="236">μm diam., globosae, in sporodochiis in hymenio vel in vitro. Sclerotia tuberoidea,</emphasis>
4–8 × 1.5–4 
<emphasis id="FAA84574FFFB2C0CF3B7FD3601419D63" box="[233,516,749,770]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="236">mm, extus nigra, intus albida.</emphasis>
</paragraph>
